{
  "stem": "11964.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And even though we had one Polish maid who would clean and take care of the house-- there was a time that we also had a Jewish cook-- but my mother would always prepare the Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And for the Shabbat, we always had fish, and we always had chicken soup and some meat or chicken.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And on Friday, very, very often my mother would make a special dish, a Jewish dish, which is called cholent.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "It is-- in English, it is spelled C-H-O-L-E-N-T.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "A cholent is a very traditional dish stemming from the fact that Jews would not cook on a Saturday.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they would take a-- a cast iron pot, and they would put good pieces of meat and potatoes and all kinds of beans and all kinds of different spices.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they would cover it with parchment paper, put a lid on it, and take it to a baker's oven.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they would leave it in the baker's oven, which would remain there unattended until the following morning, where we would retrieve the pot.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we would bring it home and then serve it as a meal.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it is absolutely delicious.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was very traditional.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This, and, of course, the baking of the challah.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember my mother was very, very careful in teaching us how to prepare the Shabbat and the intricate way of-- of baking the challah and folding the challah pieces, braiding the challah.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And of course, we learned how to prepare the fish, the gefilte fish, which were different from the gefilte fish we know now in America.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We actually stuffed-- 'gefilte' means 'stuffed.' And we actually stuffed the fish.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We would retain the-- the skin, and we would remove the meat.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
